[3] Peru (Cusco)
Date: Mon 5 Nov 2018
Source: La Republica [translated online, edited]
https://larepublica.pe/sociedad/1351730-cusco-region-insistira-minsa-declaratoria-emergencia-sarampion


Cusco will declare a measles emergency. Despite the fact that 72 suspected measles cases have been reported in Cusco, the Ministry of Health did not declare the region a health emergency. Authorities will request reconsideration.

In spite of the request of the health authorities of Cusco, the executive decided not to declare a health alert regarding measles to the imperial region. The decision has concerned the regional Director of Mealth, Javier Stamp Vera, because there is a significant increase in cases of this disease.

The Ministry of Health (MINSA), through a document addressed to the Regional Directorate, indicated that a national vaccination campaign will be held, so that an emergency declaration is not necessary.

To this end, a new request will be issued, where they request to reconsider the measure of the MINSA. They will also enclose reports of the 72 suspected cases of measles and the 5 confirmed cases so far.

