[5] Philippines (Visayas)
Date: Sat 2 Nov 2018
Source: Big News Network [edited]
https://www.bignewsnetwork.com/news/258257034/measles-alert-up-in-cv-doh-sets-free-kids-immunization


A person infected with the virus [measles] can pass the disease to at least 20 persons who happen to personally touch the patient or are within the vicinity when the carrier coughs or sneezes, according to the Department of Health Center for Health Development (DOH CHD).

Although preventable by immunization, measles with its complications is still the leading cause of death among preventable diseases, Dr. Cortez added.

In 2017, DOH authorities declared a measles outbreak in Zamboanga, and another outbreak was later noted in Luzon, according to Ruff Vincent Valdevieso.

Doctors Cesar Tomas Lopez and Jeanette Pauline Arellano-Cortez said that the measles vaccine the DOH would be using has been tried and tested effective since 1970's and is still the best community protection against the viral measles infection.

With proximity to Zamboanga, the DOH-7 Regional Epidemiology and Surveillance Unit sounded the alarm over what they perceive as danger signs of possible entry of the virus into the Visayas. A regular boat trip services Dumaguete and Zamboanga.

According to data from the RESU, from January to 27 Oct 2018, there has been a total of 305 cases of measles monitored in Central Visayas.

Of all the cases, 15% (45 patients) are from Dumaguete, 28 patients (9.1%) from Bacong Negros Oriental, 5.9 % (17 cases) from Sibulan, and in Negros Oriental and in Larena Siquijor 5.5%, RESU7 said. Cebu City this year [2018] has some 25 measles cases monitored, this is 8.1% of the cases here. The disease has also caused one death, based on reports from different disease reporting units (DRUs) of the DOH.

In 2016, the same period saw 45 cases and no deaths; that is why this year [2018], health authorities say cases are 582% higher, Valdeviesa, who is a nurse, reported.

RESU 7 also pointed out that the ages of their monitored cases ranged from 5-60 years old.

While Bohol Province has but yet 12 suspected measles cases, there is only one laboratory confirmed measles case and another rubella case, the regional center for disease monitoring shared. But with twice daily sea trips from Dumaguete to Tagbilaran, what are the chances that the disease could be spread in Bohol? High, health authorities said.

To respond to the alarming situation, DOH now brings a region-wide Supplemental Immunization Activity (SIA) in Central Visayas from 22 Oct-23 Nov 2018.

Dr. Cortez explained that the Measles Containing Vaccine (MVC), a vaccine that has been used since 1970s, would be used in the month-long activity.

Targets are children from 6 weeks (1 month and 2 weeks) to 59 months, or 4 years and 11 months, according to DOH.

